The paper deals with the segmentation of optic disc and cup in fundus images using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised domain adaptation framework using adversarial learning, which involves training a neural network to learn from a source domain and generalize to a target domain. This falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves image processing techniques, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of uncertainty maps to improve segmentation performance, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
